cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "bellwether: cost-and-failure-mode benchmark for LLM agents"
message: >-
  If you use bellwether or its methodology in your work, please cite it
  using the metadata below.
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Stephen
    family-names: Hedrick
    email: Stephen@wavebound.io
repository-code: "https://github.com/cartesianxr7/bellwether"
url: "https://cartesianxr7.github.io/bellwether/"
abstract: >-
  Cross-provider LLM benchmark and Python package for procurement-style
  evaluation. Defines and implements effective_TCoT (total cost per
  successful task completion, including failed-attempt waste) and an
  eight-mode failure-mode taxonomy. Machine-checkable ground truth, no
  LLM-as-judge.
keywords:
  - llm
  - benchmark
  - evaluation
  - agents
  - procurement
  - tcot
license: MIT
version: 0.4.0
date-released: "2026-05-08"
